{"word":"H6342 - פָּחַד - pâchad - paw-kkad' - Be afraid","slug":"H6342","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">פָּחַד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>pâchad"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>paw-kkad'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Be afraid"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E4;&#x05BC;&#x05D7;&#x05D3; - pa&#x0302;chad</b> - <i>paw-khad'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>be startled</i> (by a sudden alarm); hence to <i>fear</i> in general: - be afraid, stand in awe, (be in) fear, make to shake."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6343\">H6343</a>, <a href=\"#/H6344\">H6344</a>, <a href=\"#/H6345\">H6345</a>, <a href=\"#/H6346\">H6346</a>"}]}